
[1]fruition

   FRUI'TION, n. [from L. fruor, to use or enjoy.]

   Use accompanied with pleasure, corporeal or intellectual; enjoyment;
   the pleasure derived from use or possession.

   If the affliction is on his body, his appetites are weakened, and
   capacity of fruition destroyed.
